The manipulandum control scheme was modified so that, instead of just following along, the human trainer could dynamically take charge and deliver a time-varying manipulative force to a patient. The goal was to use an intuitive approach. For example, if a trainer wants to assist with foot clearance, the trainer should be able to lift and deflect the manipulandum upwards at the appropriate time in the gait cycle. Further, the more the trainer pushes on the manipulandum, the more the manipulandum should deflect, and the force transmitted to the patient should increase (within limits). This deflection is captured by \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
