Permutation tests were used to evaluate differences among sample means [74]. Such tests were chosen as they are applicable to small samples and do not require distributional assumptions [75]. All data processing and statistical analyses were performed in MATLAB (R2020a, MathWorks Inc., Natick MA). One-sample permutation tests were used to test for significant differences from zero for the interaction force \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
